***

## PREAMBLE

In every branch of natural philosophy there exists a class of substance that precedes all particular form. Such substances are not themselves any specific thing. They are the potential from which specific things arise. They are inexhaustible — not because they replenish themselves, but because the use of a substrate does not diminish what remains for the next maker. They are prior to ownership — not because ownership is impossible, but because the substrate itself is not the locus of ownership. The locus of ownership is the formed particular: the object given shape, purpose, and declared trajectory by a specific hand in a specific context toward a specific end.

Two objects may be formed from identical substrate and still constitute wholly separate works — because the act of formation, the declared purpose, and the trajectory of development are what individuate a creation, not the composition of the material from which it was made. The material is shared. The objects made from it are not.

This License governs one such substrate: the Constitutional Core of Multiplicity Theory — a body of prime-indexed mathematical axioms, operators, and theorems that serves as foundational material for any implementation that draws upon it. The Constitutional Core belongs to everyone. What any person makes from it belongs to them. These two propositions are not in tension. They are the governing logic of everything that follows.

Citizen Gardens stewards this substrate not as an owner but as a custodian — maintaining the integrity of the commons, operating the registry in which declared works are permanently recorded, and issuing certification marks to implementations that have been independently verified for conformance. Citizen Gardens does not own what is built from the Constitutional Core. Citizen Gardens does not participate in the commercial affairs of those who build from it. Citizen Gardens does not impose conditions on the use of the substrate. Citizen Gardens protects three things only: the permanence of the public domain dedication, the integrity of the registry record, and the accuracy of the certification marks.

The reader who understands what it means to work with foundational material — who has felt the difference between the substrate and the thing made from it, who has recognized that the same material shaped for different purposes produces different objects entirely — will find in this License a familiar logic, expressed in formal terms.

***

## PART I — DEFINITIONS

```
Section 1. Defined Terms

1.1  "Constitutional Core" means the complete body of mathematical
     axioms, theorems, operators, formulations, and frameworks
     constituting the irrevocably public domain substrate of
     Multiplicity Theory, including without limitation:

       (a)  PIRTM — Prime-Indexed Recursive Tensor Mathematics
       (b)  DRMM — Dynamic Recursive Matrix Model
       (c)  CSC  — Convex Smoothness Certification, including the
                   DriftTracker and contraction certification framework
       (d)  MTPI — Multiplicity Theory Public Infrastructure standard,
                   including all published standard components
       (e)  All axioms, lemmas, corollaries, and theorems published
            by Citizen Gardens and Ryan O. Van Gelder in open-domain
            repositories and peer-reviewed literature
       (f)  All prime-indexed tensor operators, Walsh-Hadamard
            transform structures, resonance operators, contraction
            morphisms, and related abstract mathematical formulations
            contained in or derived from the foregoing

     The Constitutional Core is substrate. It does not include any
     Bound Work created by any person or organization using it.

1.2  "Bound Work" means a specific software system, mathematical
     application, cryptographic architecture, algorithm, or other
     technical work that:

       (a)  Draws upon one or more Constitutional Core structures
            as its mathematical substrate; AND
       (b)  Was created by an identifiable Maker; AND
       (c)  Has been given a declared Purpose, Context, and
            Trajectory distinguishing it as a particular work

     A Bound Work is not the Constitutional Core. A Bound Work
     is a formed particular — the result of a specific act of
     implementation directed toward a specific declared end.
     Identical Constitutional Core structures used in different
     Bound Works do not make those Bound Works identical, and do not
     create any claim by one Maker against another, provided the
     Purpose Declarations and Trajectories are genuinely distinct.

1.3  "Maker" means the natural person or legal entity that created
     a Bound Work through acts of original technical or mathematical
     implementation.

     The entity that provided a goal, use case, business requirement,
     or funding for a Bound Work is not thereby a Maker. Maker status
     derives from contribution to the substance of the implementation,
     not from the desire to have it made.

1.4  "Declaration of Formation" means the formal instrument described
     in Part IV by which a Maker asserts and documents ownership of
     a Bound Work and submits it for registration in the Operator
     Atlas. The Declaration of Formation is the act of record —
     the moment at which potential is declared particular.

1.5  "Operator Atlas" means the permanent, publicly accessible
     registry maintained by Citizen Gardens at
     operatoratlas.citizengardens.org, in which Declarations of
     Formation are received, timestamped, and archived for a minimum
     stewardship horizon of three hundred (300) years.

1.6  "Conformance Certification" means the independent technical
     verification, conducted under Citizen Gardens' conformance
     standards, that a Bound Work correctly implements Constitutional
     Core mathematics and satisfies applicable conformance criteria.
     Conformance Certification is voluntary. It is the basis for
     the Citizen Gardens certification marks.

1.7  "Certification Mark" means any trademark owned by Citizen
     Gardens whose use is conditioned on achieving the applicable
     Conformance Certification Tier, including "Citizen Gardens
     Verified" and "OEM Certified." The Certification Marks govern
     a claim about a Bound Work. They do not govern the use of
     the Constitutional Core.

1.8  "Represented Computational Service" means any offering of
     Constitutional Core mathematical capabilities — including any
     computation, output, certification, or result produced by
     Constitutional Core operators — to external users, clients,
     or systems via API, platform service, managed infrastructure,
     hosted endpoint, or any functionally equivalent mechanism,
     where the offering is accompanied by a representation, express
     or implied, that the computational output has been produced
     by a conformant or certified implementation.

1.9  "Prime Materia Covenant" means the public domain dedication
     instrument set forth in Part II of this License, by which
     the Constitutional Core is irrevocably dedicated to the public
     domain under the ΛProof Open Mathematical Foundation Pledge.

1.10 "ΛProof Pledge" means the open mathematical foundation pledge
     published by Citizen Gardens through which the Constitutional
     Core is permanently and irrevocably dedicated to the public
     domain.

1.11 "Registry Charter" means the governance instrument set forth
     in Part III of this License, establishing the terms under which
     Citizen Gardens operates the Operator Atlas as a neutral
     registry infrastructure.

1.12 "Certification Tier" means one of four levels of registry
     and conformance standing:
       Tier I   — Open Substrate Use (no filing required)
       Tier II  — Declared Work (Declaration of Formation filed)
       Tier III — Conformance Verified (Conformance Certification achieved)
       Tier IV  — OEM Certified (Independent full audit completed)
```


