## PART VI — CERTIFICATION TIERS

```
Section 6. The Four Tiers of Registry and Conformance Standing

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
TIER I — OPEN SUBSTRATE USE
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Who:       Any person or legal entity, anywhere, at any time
Rights:    All rights enumerated in Section 2.2
Limits:    No Operator Atlas record; no Certification Mark rights;
           no documented prior art anchor
Filing:    Not required
Cost:      None
Use case:  Academic research; individual study; internal prototyping;
           educational use; exploratory development

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
TIER II — DECLARED WORK
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Who:       Any Maker who files a complete Declaration of Formation
Rights:    All Tier I rights, plus:
             Permanent Operator Atlas Identifier and timestamp
             Documented prior art record
             Documented ownership claim for the Bound Work
             Basis for asserting ownership against later filers
             Protection of Purpose and Context from later-filing
               Makers in the same declared domain
Limits:    No Certification Mark rights
           No right to represent the Bound Work as Conformance
             Verified by Citizen Gardens
Filing:    Required Declaration of Formation (Section 4)
Cost:      None — filing is free
Use case:  Independent developers; researchers; open-source projects;
           early-stage commercial implementations not yet requiring
           third-party conformance verification

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
TIER III — CONFORMANCE VERIFIED
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Who:       Makers whose Tier II filing is followed by successful
           Conformance Certification
Rights:    All Tier II rights, plus:
             Authorization to display "Citizen Gardens Verified" mark
             Conformance certification record (cryptographically logged)
             Listing in the Operator Atlas Verified registry
             Authorization to represent the Bound Work as
               Conformance Certified by Citizen Gardens
Limits:    Certification Mark rights extend only to the Purpose
           and Context declared in the Maker's Declaration of
           Formation; use beyond declared scope is unauthorized
Filing:    Active Tier II Declaration required as prerequisite
Cost:      Voluntary contribution covering actual conformance audit
           costs; subsidized for nonprofit and academic Makers;
           fee schedule published at citizengardens.org/conformance
Use case:  Commercial deployments; investor-facing products;
           regulated industries; implementations intended to be
           represented to third parties as conformant

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
TIER IV — OEM CERTIFIED
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Who:       Makers who achieve Tier III and complete full
           independent audit
Rights:    All Tier III rights, plus:
             Authorization to display "OEM Certified" mark
             Use of "OEM Certified" in regulatory, commercial,
               and investor contexts including healthcare, finance,
               legal, and government
             Citizen Gardens certification letter
             Regulatory-grade documentation package
             Named listing in Citizen Gardens Annual Report
             Priority technical support
Filing:    Active Tier III certification required as prerequisite
Cost:      Voluntary contribution covering actual independent
           audit costs; fee schedule published at
           citizengardens.org/oem
Use case:  Enterprise deployments; regulated industry compliance;
           government procurement; healthcare, financial services,
           and legal technology
```


***

## PART VII — THE BOUND WORKS MARK LICENSE

### *Governing Use of Citizen Gardens Certification Marks*

```
Section 7. Certification Mark Terms

7.1  WHAT THIS PART GOVERNS. This Part VII governs one thing only:
     the use of the Certification Marks — "Citizen Gardens Verified"
     and "OEM Certified" — which are trademarks owned by Citizen
     Gardens.

     This Part does not govern:
       (a)  Use of the Constitutional Core (governed by Part II)
       (b)  Use of any Bound Work (governed by the Maker's own license)
       (c)  Any commercial activity of any Maker
       (d)  Any transaction between a Maker and the Maker's customers

7.2  THE MARKS GOVERN CLAIMS, NOT MATH. The Certification Marks
     are representations about a Bound Work's conformance status.
     They are instruments of market information — a signal to
     investors, counterparties, regulators, and the public that
     an independent technical verification has been performed.

     The Constitutional Core requires no mark. It is public domain.
     The marks exist to distinguish verified implementations from
     unverified ones — a distinction that matters commercially,
     does not restrict mathematically, and is enforced only at
     the level of the representation, never at the level of use.

7.3  PERMITTED MARK USE. A Maker holding the applicable
     Certification Tier may:

       (a)  Display the applicable Certification Mark on products,
            documentation, presentations, and marketing materials
            describing the certified Bound Work
       (b)  Represent, in commercial and regulatory contexts, that
            the Bound Work is Citizen Gardens Verified or OEM
            Certified, as applicable
       (c)  Include the Operator Atlas Identifier alongside the
            Certification Mark to enable public verification

7.4  PROHIBITED MARK USE. No person or entity may:

       (a)  Display any Certification Mark in connection with a
            Bound Work that has not achieved the corresponding
            Certification Tier
       (b)  Represent to any third party that a Bound Work has
            been Conformance Certified by Citizen Gardens in the
            absence of a valid, current Certification Tier record
            in the Operator Atlas
       (c)  Use any mark, name, logo, or representation that is
            confusingly similar to the Certification Marks in
            connection with any representation about Constitutional
            Core conformance

7.5  REPRESENTED COMPUTATIONAL SERVICE STANDARD. A Maker who offers
     a Represented Computational Service must hold at minimum
     Tier III Conformance Certification for the declared Purpose and
     Context within which the service is offered.

     A Maker may operate a computational service using Constitutional
     Core mathematics without Tier III certification. What such a
     Maker may not do is represent that service as conformant,
     certified, or verified by Citizen Gardens, or use the
     Certification Marks in connection with it.

     The distinction is between the service (unaffected by this
     License) and the representation (governed by this Part VII
     and by trademark law).

7.6  MARK LICENSE GRANT. Subject to the requirements of Section 7.4
     and the applicable Certification Tier holding:

     Citizen Gardens grants to each Maker holding an applicable
     Certification Tier a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable,
     revocable license to use the corresponding Certification Mark
     solely:

       (a)  In connection with the Bound Work identified in the
            Maker's Declaration of Formation
       (b)  Within the Purpose and Context declared in that filing
       (c)  In a manner consistent with Citizen Gardens' published
            mark usage guidelines

7.7  MARK LICENSE TERMINATION. The mark license granted in
     Section 7.6 terminates automatically if:

       (a)  The Maker's Certification Tier lapses or is withdrawn
            due to non-renewal, violation, or Technical Review
            Panel determination
       (b)  The Maker files a patent application covering
            Constitutional Core mathematics (Section 5.2)
       (c)  The Maker initiates patent litigation against another
            person's good-faith Constitutional Core use (Section 5.4)
       (d)  The Maker's Declaration of Formation is found to contain
            material false statements of attribution (Section 3.8)

     Termination requires the Maker to immediately cease all
     use of the Certification Marks and remove them from all
     materials within thirty (30) days.

7.8  DONATIONS AND REGISTRY ECONOMICS. Citizen Gardens accepts
     voluntary contributions from Makers and the public in support
     of registry operations, conformance infrastructure, and
     long-term archival stewardship.

     Citizen Gardens does not:
       (a)  Charge a fee for Tier I or Tier II standing
       (b)  Charge a fee as a percentage of any Maker's revenue
       (c)  Receive royalties from any Bound Work
       (d)  Take equity in any enterprise that files a Declaration
       (e)  Participate in any commercial transaction between
            a Maker and the Maker's customers

     Conformance audit contributions (Tiers III and IV) are
     calibrated to cover actual audit costs. Excess contributions
     fund subsidized certification for nonprofit and academic Makers
     and the 300-year stewardship endowment.

     Citizen Gardens makes the same amount regardless of whether
     a certified Bound Work generates zero revenue or transforms
     an industry. The registry serves the commons. It is not a
     participant in the market.
```


