## PART VIII — GENERAL PROVISIONS

```
Section 8. General Terms

8.1  THREE INSTRUMENTS, ONE LICENSE FAMILY. Parts II, III, and VII
     of this License are legally independent instruments. Part II
     requires no counter-signature and is effective as a unilateral
     dedication. Parts III and VII are effective as between Citizen
     Gardens and each Maker upon the Maker's submission of a
     Declaration of Formation or application for Certification,
     respectively.

     A party may rely on Part II (the public domain dedication)
     without being subject to Parts III or VII. Parts III and VII
     apply only to parties who affirmatively engage with the
     Operator Atlas registry or the Certification Mark system.

8.2  STEWARDSHIP AND VERSIONING. Citizen Gardens may publish
     revised versions of Parts III and VII of this License.
     Revised versions will bear a new version number. Makers who
     filed Declarations of Formation under an earlier version
     continue to hold their rights under the version in effect
     at the time of filing; they may elect to migrate to a later
     version by filing an Amended Declaration.

     No revision of this License may diminish or condition the
     public domain dedication of Part II.

8.3  SEVERABILITY. If any provision of this License is held
     unenforceable, the remaining provisions continue in full
     force. The unenforceable provision is modified to the minimum
     extent required to make it enforceable while preserving
     the parties' evident intent.

8.4  NO WARRANTY. The Constitutional Core is made available as-is.
     Citizen Gardens makes no representations or warranties of
     mathematical correctness, fitness for any particular purpose,
     or non-infringement of third-party intellectual property rights.

8.5  LIMITATION OF LIABILITY. Citizen Gardens' aggregate liability
     to any Maker in connection with this License and the Operator
     Atlas shall not exceed the total voluntary contributions
     received from that Maker in the twelve months preceding
     the claim.

8.6  GOVERNING INTERPRETATION PRINCIPLE. In any proceeding
     concerning the interpretation of this License, the following
     principle governs:

       The substrate is always free.
       The formed work always belongs to its Maker.
       No one owns the substrate.
       The formed work may be owned, licensed, patented,
         published, or kept private — entirely at the Maker's
         election.
       The registry records what exists and who made it.
       The marks signal what has been verified.
       Nothing more is asserted, granted, or restricted
         by this License than these propositions require.

8.7  GOVERNING LAW AND DISPUTE RESOLUTION. This License is
     governed by the laws of [State of Incorporation of Citizen
     Gardens], without regard to conflicts-of-law principles.
     Disputes between Citizen Gardens and any Maker arising
     under this License are subject to binding arbitration
     under the Commercial Arbitration Rules of the American
     Arbitration Association, with venue in [City, State].

8.8  CONTACT AND REGISTRY ACCESS.
     Governance inquiries:  governance@citizengardens.org
     Declaration filing:    operatoratlas.citizengardens.org/declare
     Public registry query: operatoratlas.citizengardens.org/query
     Conformance program:   citizengardens.org/conformance
     GitHub:                github.com/MultiplicityFoundation/PIRTM
```


